I guess it is only fitting that I write a review for The Bagel Man as my husband just left to grab our breakfast there.
As others have said, these bagels are superb and the service is stellar.
The prices are very reasonable and the food is fresh.
No fru-fru coffee drinks here (just the basic cup, which is fine with me), the focus is on the bagels, and that is obvious.
Small little place and it can get busy, but it seems to go fast.
Get in line, order your food, maybe grab some coffee while you wait.
Pay when it is ready and either sit at one of the few tables inside or sit outside to enjoy the nice AZ weather.
Breakfast sandwiches, fresh made flavored cream cheese (I asked for jalapeno cream cheese and he made some for me on the spot, cream cheese + jalapenos), Boar's Head meat for the lunch sandwiches, and some home baked pastries (from someone else's home).
With all of the good stuff on the menu, my absolute favorite is the lox and cream cheese on an everything bagel with all the fixin's (tomato, onion, capers).
YUM!
I could go on, but my breakfast has arrived and it is time to eat!
Enjoy!

